WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Hi everyone!

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Hi everyone!

3
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:05.000
My name is Kirill.

4
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:06.000
My name is Darina.

5
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Today we came to the Socio-Pedagogical Institute.

6
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:17.000
We wanted to learn more about it, get to know it,

7
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:24.000
learn more about the teachers and get acquainted with the students here.

8
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
And I still don't know where I'm going to apply or what profession

9
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
I didn't know that either back in my time.

10
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
But my friend helped me with that — he inspired me,

11
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.000
told me what to do and where to go.

12
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.000
And now let me give you a mini-tour of this institute.

13
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.000
So, did Kirill learn it?

14
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Yes.

15
00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:56.000
Yes.

16
00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.000
So far we like everything,

17
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.000
it's a bit confusing with so many corridors.

18
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
because my life is going to be wonderful.

19
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.480
And we've been here before — we had career guidance here

20
00:01:23.480 --> 00:01:27.480
Oh, not bad

21
00:01:27.480 --> 00:01:28.580
We had a competition here, we came last place.

22
00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:30.480
Here, really?

23
00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:31.480
Yes.

24
00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:33.480
Well, this is the Assembly Hall.

25
00:01:38.480 --> 00:01:43.480
Lectures are held here, and here is a special stand.

26
00:01:43.480 --> 00:01:44.480
What is it called? Does anyone know?

27
00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:45.480
A podium. (the operator said)

28
00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:46.480
What?

29
00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:47.480
Who knows?

30
00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:48.480
A podium. (overheard the operator's answer)

31
00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:56.480
Where should I sit? Kirill, come on, organize it!

32
00:01:56.480 --> 00:01:57.480
Well, sit here.

33
00:01:58.480 --> 00:01:59.480
Everything is fine.

34
00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:04.480
Guys, we decided to interview a student

35
00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:07.480
of the Socio-Pedagogical Institute — Pasha.

36
00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:10.480
Hi, my name is Pasha.

37
00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:15.480
As you already know, I'm studying in my second year in the program

38
00:02:15.480 --> 00:02:20.480
Pedagogical Education with two majors in Biology and Chemistry, already in second year.

39
00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:24.480
I expressed my desire to enter our Socio-Pedagogical Institute

40
00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:27.480
while still studying in 11th grade.

41
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:30.480
I had a goal, and I achieved it.

42
00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:33.480
I passed the EGE (the Russian national school-leaving exam after 11th grade) quite well and enrolled.

43
00:02:33.480 --> 00:02:35.480
And what profession do you want to go into afterwards?

44
00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:45.480
I haven't really thought about it yet — I'll keep studying and getting my education.

45
00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:48.480
Why did you decide to leave after 11th grade and not after 9th grade?

46
00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:55.480
In my opinion it was easier to enroll and less time is spent that way.

47
00:02:55.480 --> 00:02:56.480
That's all.

48
00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:57.480
Wait, after 11th grade? (operator)

49
00:02:57.480 --> 00:02:58.480
Yes.

50
00:02:58.480 --> 00:02:59.480
How so? (operator)

51
00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:00.480
Why less time? (operator)

52
00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:06.480
Less time, because college takes more time.

53
00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:07.480
Really? (operator)

54
00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:08.480
Yes, two extra years.

55
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:15.480
So it turns out that if someone left after 9th grade, from among my peers, so to speak,

56
00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:17.480
they are already...

57
00:03:17.480 --> 00:03:20.480
They are still studying at college

58
00:03:20.480 --> 00:03:22.480
Or possibly already finished.

59
00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:26.480
And this year they graduate and only then enroll in the first year

60
00:03:26.480 --> 00:03:28.480
of higher education.

61
00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:30.480
Let's imagine you're already a teacher. (operator)

62
00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:33.480
So, the EGE — what ones are you planning to give.

63
00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:36.480
Are you going to give EGE exams at all?

64
00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:37.480
What's on your plan?

65
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:38.480
When I finish 11th grade

66
00:03:38.480 --> 00:03:39.480
Go on

67
00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:41.480
Social Studies, History, English

68
00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:44.480
I'll be taking 5 exams.

69
00:03:45.480 --> 00:03:46.480
A lot, a lot.

70
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:47.480
Are you ready at all?

71
00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:50.480
Well, it's in progress

72
00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.480
Well, I'm ready for the OGE (the Russian national exam after 9th grade)

73
00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:52.480
For now you need to pass the OGE, right?

74
00:03:52.480 --> 00:03:53.580
Yes.

75
00:03:53.480 --> 00:03:55.480
Well, that's easy, not hard.

76
00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:58.480
Pasha, can you give some advice on passing the EGE? (operator)

77
00:03:58.480 --> 00:04:00.480
Because a lot of people are scared of the EGE. (operator)

78
00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:04.480
EGE, EGE, EGE — there's no need to be afraid

79
00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:09.480
It's all quite systematic.

80
00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:13.480
Every day, even just a little, do practice variants.

81
00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:17.480
You'll notice they're roughly the same.

82
00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:21.480
You'll build up, gain knowledge, gain experience, and then

83
00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:26.480
you'll pass that exam with confidence.

84
00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:29.480
Alright, shall we let our dear guest go. (operator)

85
00:04:29.480 --> 00:04:30.480
Yes, thank you very much.

86
00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:31.480
Thank you.

87
00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:34.480
Well, our video is coming to an end.

88
00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:36.480
I am very glad that the guys came to us.

89
00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:42.480
I'm very pleased that they walked around, had a look, met the teachers and the students.

90
00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:44.480
So, what can be said?

91
00:04:44.480 --> 00:04:49.480
That, guys, there is a whole life ahead, a whole journey, a whole road.

92
00:04:49.480 --> 00:04:52.480
And it's important to make the right decision at the right time.

93
00:04:52.480 --> 00:04:58.480
So use your head, be smart, be kind and well-mannered

94
00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:00.480
And everything will be fine.

95
00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:01.480
That's it.

96
00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:04.480
Goodbye everyone.

97
00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:10.480
Subscribe to Sotsium, subscribe to our group Prodolzheniye (Continuation).

98
00:05:10.480 --> 00:05:16.480
When we were all studying together, we had Media and Advertising classes.

99
00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:19.480
As a practice project we decided to shoot this full-length video.

100
00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:22.480
So be sure to subscribe and follow us.

101
00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:24.480
We will continue to do something big and beautiful.

102
00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:26.480
Alright, bye.
